On 20 February 2022, around 7000 people, including representatives of National Corps, staged a Unity March in Odessa. The organizers of the march emphasized that Odessa was, is, and will be a Ukrainian city. Some of them carried flags of Ukraine, as well as banners with 'Unity is Ukraine' written on them. Protesters were also chanting slogans calling for unity. [size=around 7000]

On 20 February 2022, people gathered in Zaporizhia to commemorate the anniversary of murder of Heavenly Hundred Heroes during the EuroMaidan Revolution. The participants emphasized that the struggle of the Ukrainian people for freedom continues, so the citizens must be united and strong. [size=no report]

On 20 February 2022, activists, including Crimean Tatars, gathered outside the court in Bakhchysarai, Crimea, in support of 15 illegally detained Crimean Tatars, who came on February 18, 2022, to the hearing of the case of one of the detained Crimean Tatar activist. [size=no report]

On 20 February 2022, around 1000 people staged a March of Unity in Lviv. The protesters carried flags of Ukraine, as well as banners with 'Ukraine is United' written on them. Protesters were also chanting slogans calling for unity. [size=around 1000]
